{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id77385d37-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s402e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"402e"},"text":"§ 402e.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Application of Federal Power Act","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The provisions of the Federal Power Act [","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s791a"},"text":"16 U.S.C. 791a","children":[],"tail":" et seq.] shall not apply to lands included in the Bryce Canyon National Park on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1930-06-13"},"text":"June 13, 1930","children":[],"tail":", nor to any lands added to said park under the authority of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s402d"},"text":"section 402d of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id77385d38-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1930-06-13/ch480/s2"},"text":"June 13, 1930, ch. 480, § 2","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/46/583"},"text":"46 Stat. 583","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id77385d39-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id77385d3a-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id77385d3b-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Federal Power Act, referred to in text, was in the original the “Act of ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1920-06-10"},"text":"June 10, 1920","children":[],"tail":", known as the Federal Water Power Act,” and was redesignated as the Federal Power Act by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s791a"},"text":"section 791a of this title","children":[],"tail":". The Federal Power Act is "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1920-06-10/ch285"},"text":"act June 10, 1920, ch. 285","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/41/1063"},"text":"41 Stat. 1063","children":[],"tail":", and is classified generally to chapter 12 (§ 791a et seq.) of this title. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s791a"},"text":"section 791a of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
